<h2>Where Vyapar genuinely wins</h2>

<h3>Hindi-first design</h3>
<p>UI in Hindi, invoice printing in Hindi, customer-facing receipts in Hindi. For a shopkeeper whose English is functional but not first-language, this removes the single biggest friction in adopting digital invoicing.</p>

<h3>Works offline on cheap Android</h3>
<p>Runs on entry-level Android phones, works without internet, syncs when connection returns. This matters more than any AI feature for the segment Vyapar serves.</p>

<h3>GST and e-way bill native</h3>
<p>Generates GST invoices in the right format, prepares GSTR-1 and GSTR-3B, handles e-way bills for transport, supports e-invoicing for businesses crossing the threshold. The compliance is well-engineered.</p>

<h3>Inventory built for Indian retail</h3>
<p>Stock by location, batch number, expiry date, low-stock alerts, sale and purchase tracking. Designed for the messy reality of Indian small-business inventory rather than abstracted SaaS workflow.</p>

<h2>Best Indian use cases</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Kirana shops and local retailers</strong>, Daily invoicing, customer ledger (udhaar), inventory tracking.</li>
  <li><strong>Electronics, hardware, mobile shops</strong>, IMEI / serial tracking, warranty management, GST billing.</li>
  <li><strong>Small wholesalers and distributors</strong>, Bulk billing, party-wise ledger, payment follow-up.</li>
  <li><strong>Contractors and service businesses</strong>, Quotation, GST bill, advance and balance tracking.</li>
  <li><strong>Restaurants and small F&amp;B</strong>, Daily sales, GST output, supplier ledger.</li>
</ul>

